step.start-script:
# Copyright 2016 ExxonMobil Corporation. All rights reserved.
''' This implements the logic formerly found in button-action::rate-change-results-icon-gda(). When the OC wants to perform a rate change, the button is pressed and the rate change final diagnosis is made true. The procedure then waits for the recommendation icon arrow to go red before launching output display to show the recommendations to download for the rate change. ''' import system from ils.sfc.common.constants import OPERATION_SCOPE,ERROR,WARNING import java.util.Date from finalDiagnosis import getBlock from util import getPost from api import s88GetData from com.ils.queue import post from lib import getWindow from ils.sfc.gateway.api import getChartLogger from time import sleep def onStart(chart,block): log = system.util.getLogger(getChartLogger(chart)) maxWait = 10.0 ws = block.get("workspace","") log.tracef("In %s with %s, a %s. . .",chart.get("name",""),block.get("name",""),"step")
# Disable rate change button in favor of restick button if cat is out. if system.tag.read("[]Site/CSTR/CAT-AND-C2-IS-IN-TIMER").getValue() == False: log.tracef("CAT and C2 are out!") post.messageToQueue(chart,block,"Cat is out. Do not use this button at this time.%s%sUse the 'Initiate Re-Stick' button on the same workspace to initiate a stick from the conditions specified in the New Setpoints column."%(str(cr),str(cr)),WARNING,block)
currentDataBlock = finalDiagnosis.getBlock(block,"em-s88-rate-change-current-data-callback") # the em-s88-rate-change-current-data-callback upon WS; newDataBlock = finalDiagnosis.getBlock(block,"em-s88-rate-change-new-data-callback") # the em-s88-rate-change-new-data-callback upon WS; winSeq = lib.getWindow(block) if < 1:
w = winSeq # ======================== Case ===================== caseArg=currentdatablock.get("configuration","") if caseArg=="single-rx": log.tracef("Handling Single-Rx") system.tag.write("[]Site/RateChange/SINGLE-RATE-CHANGE-INPUT",False)
sleep(system.tag.read("[]Site/G2-LATENCY-TIME").getValue()) system.tag.write("[]Site/RateChange/SINGLE-RATE-CHANGE-INPUT",True)
elif caseArg=="series-rx": system.tag.write("[]Site/RateChange/SERIES-RATE-CHANGE-INPUT",False)
sleep(system.tag.read("[]Site/G2-LATENCY-TIME").getValue()) system.tag.write("[]Site/RateChange/SERIES-RATE-CHANGE-INPUT",True)
elif caseArg=="split-fd-rx": system.tag.write("[]Site/RateChange/SPLIT-RATE-CHANGE-INPUT",False)
sleep(system.tag.read("[]Site/G2-LATENCY-TIME").getValue()) system.tag.write("[]Site/RateChange/SPLIT-RATE-CHANGE-INPUT",True)
elif caseArg=="c-rx": system.tag.write("[]Site/RateChange/CRX-RATE-CHANGE-INPUT",False)
sleep(system.tag.read("[]Site/G2-LATENCY-TIME").getValue()) system.tag.write("[]Site/RateChange/CRX-RATE-CHANGE-INPUT",True)
else: post.messageToQueue(chart,block,"%s could not determine reactor type to use <%s>."%("emS88TransferData.onStart",currentdatablock.get("configuration","")),ERROR,block)
log.tracef("Waiting for the setpoints to be enunciated to the post.)") startWait = Date().toString() status,post=api.s88GetData(chart,block,"post.val",OPERATION_SCOPE) postIndex = util.getPost(post) while True: if postIndex == "red" or Date().toString() - startWait > maxWait: break; sleep(1.0) log.tracef("Cleaning up and showing extra workspace, if desired.") # Display rate change reminder for OC required actions after rate change try: currentGrade = round(system.tag.read("[]DiagnosticToolkit/CSTR/RLA3-Current-Grade/value").getValue()) except: currentGrade = 3666.0 # STATUS, CURRENT_RATE = call s88-get-data(CURRENT-DATA-BLOCK, "poly-rate.val", s88-local); STATUS, NEW_RATE = call s88-get-data(NEW-DATA-BLOCK, "poly-rate.val", s88-local); call calc-new-rx-mst-target(CURRENT_RATE, NEW_RATE); if currentGrade == 3666.0: w
log.tracef("Complete!")
